<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08164m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08164m">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08164m"> 164(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Paddy&apos;s opera / service at S. Patricks / Sir Robt Stewart</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>A Distinguished Irish Musician / Sir C. Villiers Stanford </b> <br>As a member of the choir at St. Patrick&apos;s and Christ Church Cathedrals, young Stanford learned his music from Joseph Robinson and from Sir Robert P. Stewart.<font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> The members of the cathedral choirs had a triple duty to perform in those days, and the story is from Christ Church at the morning service they had to go to the Castle Chapel and in the evening to &ldquo;Paddy&apos;s Opera,&rdquo; which was the irreverent way some of them referred to the service at St. Patrick&apos;s Cathedral. <small> <a name="II9feb24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#II9feb24"><cite title="source">Irish Independent</cite></a> (9 February 1924) 4/5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
